Summary: Bright object over the Bad Lands.
divs: Sighting DetailsAt about 300 am I left my tent in the Sage Creek Wilderness of the Bad Lands National Park to "do my business". The sky was absolutely clear and visability was unlimited. Standing on top of a small knoll on the high prarie I was looking due south when I noticed a bright spherical object on a low trajectory moving slowly west to east approximately 5 miles away. It was about 5 to 10 degrees above the horizon when it dropped below a small hill. I was in Air Force Tactical aircrew for 7 years an can identify most of the worlds aircraft and can tell a satelite from an aircraft. This was niether and as there was no airfields for a 100 miles in that direction I found it very disconcerting.
